<cell alignment="block" valignment="top" topline="true" leftline="true" rightline="true" usebox="none">
\begin_inset Text

\begin_layout Plain Layout
For the classification of zero knowledge proof, it is required that a probabilis
tic polynomial-time bounded verifier is not tricked by an unbounded prover.
 In contrast, an argument relates to a relaxed soundness property, where
 the adversarial prover is limited to computational feasible implementations
 based on polynomial sized circuits.
 The relaxation has been introduced by Brassard et.al.
 When the distinction between proof and argument is not explicitly required,
 the term protocol is used by some authors.
\end_layout

\end_inset
</cell>
